# Cluster Context

## OpenShift Cluster
- API: `https://api.ocp.kounex.com:6443`
- Apps domain: `*.apps.ocp.kounex.com`
- Default storage class: `lvms-vg1`
- Managed by OpenShift GitOps operator

## ArgoCD
- Namespace: `openshift-gitops`
- Route: `https://openshift-gitops-server-openshift-gitops.apps.ocp.kounex.com`
- Admin credentials stored in secret `openshift-gitops-cluster` in `openshift-gitops` namespace
- App-of-apps pattern:
  - `apps-manager` (root) -> per-app parent (e.g. `bracket-app`) -> child apps (e.g. `bracket-db`, `bracket-frontend`)
  - Parent apps use Kustomize, pointing to `manifests/apps/<app-name>/apps` in this repo
  - Child apps are ArgoCD Application CRDs managed by their parent

## MCP Servers
- `user-kubernetes` — general cluster operations (pods, deployments, services, logs)
- `user-argocd` — ArgoCD API (list/get/sync/delete applications, resource trees, events, logs)

Use the ArgoCD MCP for application-level operations (sync, status, rollback). Use the Kubernetes MCP for lower-level cluster inspection (pod logs, describe resources, exec).
